The code above reproduces the problem, but I found an additional case where it doesn't work.  If the decorated function is imported, it will still jump to the decorator. Changing `filter_follow_imports` to this seems to fix both cases:

```
        def filter_follow_imports(names):
            for name in names:
                if isinstance(name, imports.ImportName):
                    for context in name.infer():
                        yield context.name
                elif isinstance(name, TreeNameDefinition) and name.tree_name.get_definition().type in ('import_name', 'import_from'):
                    for context in imports.infer_import(name.parent_context, name.tree_name, is_goto=True):
                        yield context
                else:
                    yield name
```

It seems like the ultimate problem is that a bunch of the code in the evaluator package needs to go down a is_goto=True path for this to work, but name.infer() doesn't pass that flag down.

