1. There is an "appveyor todo" list at the top, it states that prebuilt binaries from Spotify Automated Builds should be used. Do not build CEF from sources.

2. There seems to be an issue with appveyor logs, they are out of order. This is not the succession in which scripts were really executed, thus you do not see the real error at the end. See this SO question: https://stackoverflow.com/questions/230751/how-to-flush-output-of-python-print . This must be fixed in all scripts in tools/ , must support Python 2 and 3 and run on all OSes (Win, Linux, Mac). It seems that `apply this to every python process in your environment with PYTHONUNBUFFERED=TRUE (and unset the variable to undo this).` in one of answers is the best option. It should be applied in each script at the beginning of main() function.

